OL,3,CWhich seven locations have been
OL,4,Cselected for government's new towns?
OL,6,FIn its manifesto, Labour pledged to
OL,7,Fbegin work on 1.5 million new homes
OL,8,Fover the course of the Parliament, to
OL,9,Fexpand homeownership to more Britons.
OL,11,FHousing Secretary Steve Reed said:
OL,12,F"People want real change ` homes they
OL,13,Fcan afford, local infrastructure that
OL,14,Fworks, and good jobs in thriving
OL,15,Fcommunities.
OL,17,F"Our next generation of new towns
OL,18,Fmarks a turning point in how we build
OL,19,Ffor the future.
